args:
I dreamed about the prince last night!
We were holding hands, and he said he
LOVED me, and...EEE! Anyway, I'm in a
great mood now.
The prince is my soul mate!

Ohmigosh, I know EXACTLY what
you mean. I dream about Luccy every.
Single. Night. So I wake up happy
every single day! Tee hee!
I'm sure he dreams about me too—he's\njust too shy to say anything.

He probably mumbles in his sleep,
like ＂Chelsea, my love, don't ever
leave me...＂ or ＂Of course you can
smell my feet...＂
Oh, I'm sure the prince dreams about\nme too. I can practically hear him now!\n＂Philia, you're my truest of true loves...＂
Tee hee... Tee hee hee!\nTEEEEEE HEE HEE HEE HEEEEEE!
All right! I'm gonna keep my ear pressed\nto Luccy's door every night from now on.\nNo winks, just eavesdropping!
Girl, that would be murder on your\ncomplexion. Lucky for you, there's\na better way.
Let me make sure I understand your\nrequest. What you wish to know is—
Every word that Luccy and the prince say\nin their sleep!
Forgive me, but such feats are beyond\nthe reach of even my auguries.
Should you seek a glimpse into the future,\nhowever, I would be most happy to oblige.
Ooo, yes please! Tell me about me and\nLuccy's wedding day!
Good idea! Then you can plan ahead for\nbad weather or party crashers or whatever.
Apparently you consider the marriage itself\na foregone conclusion... But perhaps that\nmeans I'll be able to see something.
Now, orbuculum, show me the future...\nHm?! No... No, it cannot be!
Too cute, right? Is Luccy in a tux?\nHow does his butt look?
I see only you, Chelsea. Stalked by the\nshadow of death.
Especially today, you must stay far away\nfrom Luca. If you do not, you will no doubt\nmeet your doom.

Oh, I believe it! I swear, when I'm next
to him my heart beats so fast I feel like
I'm gonna keel over right then and there.
Tee hee!

Uh... Chelsea? This sounds pretty serious.
Maybe just play it safe for today, yeah?
Luca's off training in the mountains,
anyway, so—
Oh, right! I better hustle up there and\nbring him some lunch.
Chelsea, you will be placing yourself\nin grave danger if you seek Luca out now.
You're right... Seeing Luccy all sweaty and\nswole is BOUND to get me in trouble!\nOh jeez, I'm drooling...
Chelsea, we're talking about LITERAL\nDEATH here. Let's you and me just\nhang out here today.
Oh, Philia. How can you say you love\nthe prince if you're afraid of a little death?
It would seem our appeals have\ngone unheard—but we must not\nallow death to claim her.

There's nothing more sacred than love.
It's what makes life worth living,
so we can't let some stinky shadow
muck things up! Let's go, Verica!
O-okay, but I'm not sure we're on the\nsame page...
A lunch box full of love!\nHmm, or maybe a love box full of lunch...?
Following her like this feels rather\nunderhanded.
Yeah, well, suck it up! We need to make\nsure she lives to see Luca again, even if\nit means getting our sneak on.
Ack! Those rocks are rolling straight\nfor Chelsea!
Luccy's gonna be so happy to see me!\nI made all his favorites, and I'm gonna\nfeed him each bite myself.
What manner of sorcery...? She's walking\nthrough the barrage as if it weren't there!
Hey! Watch it, you dumb rocks!\nThis basket is full of goodies for\nmy honey bun!
She seems more concerned about the\nbasket than her own body. This must be\nthe power of love... Wait! Oh no!
She may have danced through those rocks\nwith ease, but that fiend looks ready\nfor a meal of its own!
Hush! I'm checking on Luccy's lunch right\nnow. You just sit there and wait, got it?
Whoa, the fiends backed off! Guess there\nreally is no stopping a lovestruck maiden\non her—huh?!
The forest is ablaze! Even Chelsea must\nrealize it would be folly to—
Aw, this mutton's gone cold. Guess I better\nwarm it up real quick...
She's using the forest fire to reheat the\nfood! Even now, she thinks only of Luca...\nHer flames of passion are burning hot!
We're about to be burning hot ourselves!
Looks like she's gonna make it. Guess she\ndidn't need us after all, huh?
Indeed. If anything, she has emerged in\nbetter shape than us.
Yeah. If I were the shadow of death or\nwhatever, I'd probably throw the towel\nin at this point.
I do hope that you're right, but...\nI'd better look into my orbuculum\nto make sure.
Aw, man... Hey, Chelsea.\nWhat are you doing here?
What do you think, silly?\nI brought you lunch!
Holy crap... Chelsea?!\nCome on, stay with me!
Did she just get struck by lightning?!
Oh my... Philia, look at Chelsea through\nmy orbuculum!
Wh-what the heck is that black shadow?
It's death, here to claim her soul.
What?! There's gotta be a way we can\nstop it, right?!
Alas, we mortals are powerless against\nthe will of death.
Hey... Who do you think you are?

What makes you think you can come
between me and my Luccy, huh?
Did YOU make him lunch? Did YOU
bring it up here? Yeah, didn't think so!
So you better step off, or I'm gonna get\nstabby. You hear me? STABBY!
She... She just chased off death itself.
How am I?! How are YOU?!
Oh, I'm great. I never feel more alive\nthan when I'm with you! Tee hee!
No mortal can best the power of death,\nand yet...
Don't you see, Verica? Death might\nbe strong, but love is stronger!\n*sniff* It's so beautiful...
Love, you say? Hmm... Powerful emotions\nHAVE been known to alter destiny.
So long as Chelsea harbors such fierce\nlove, I suspect she'll be able to endure\nany number of fate's cruel twists.
Here comes the mutton train, Luccy!\nOpen wiiiiide!
